experiences.description:
Leader of the Toronto Restructuring practice and national working capital initiative.

- Led on site operational and financial restructuring of a copper mine in Mexico, overseeing construction and operations and the transition of control to new Korean ownership and management under a stabilized financial structure;

- Acted as interim Chief Credit Officer overseeing $750M portfolio of oil and gas accounts receivable across 5 divisions and 20k+ accounts. Updated processes and procedures, built and installed new credit risk model to reflect strategic goals of Company;

- Planned and implemented a process to manage the realization of a distressed real estate portfolio containing over 300 residential income properties which were the subject of an ongoing and coordinated fraud investigation at a major Canadian financial institution;

